subject: p15378103
History: Status post CABG, evaluation of effusions.
Findings: As compared to the previous radiograph, the right and left pleural effusions are virtually unchanged. They are mild-to-moderate in extent. The effusions are at the source of bilateral areas of compression atelectasis. Unchanged borderline size of the cardiac silhouette. No evidence of pneumonia. Unchanged right internal jugular vein catheter and left pectoral pacemaker. No pneumothorax.
